Usage: create_ccopt_clock_spine [-help] [-hard] -name <name> [-x <x>]
                                [-xmax <xmax>] [-xmin <xmin>] [-y <y>]
                                [-ymax <ymax>] [-ymin <ymin>]

-help                     # Prints out the command usage
-hard                     # If present, create a hard clock spine
                          # (bool, optional)
-name <name>              # user-defined identifier for this clock spine
                          # (string, required)
-x <x>                    # The X value of a vertical clock spine's target line
                          # (float, optional)
-xmax <xmax>              # The maximum X value of objects on a horizontal
                          # spine, and the right edge of the hard spine area
                          # (float, optional)
-xmin <xmin>              # The minimum X value of objects on a horizontal
                          # spine, and the left edge of the hard spine area
                          # (float, optional)
-y <y>                    # The Y value of a horizontal clock spine's target
                          # line (float, optional)
-ymax <ymax>              # The maximum Y value of objects on a vertical spine,
                          # and the top edge of the hard spine area
                          # (float, optional)
-ymin <ymin>              # The minimum Y value of objects on a vertical spine,
                          # and the bottom edge of the hard spine area
                          # (float, optional)